articles.title: Ireland win European Championship for Small Countries after victory over Malta - The42
articles.description: The result completes the double for head coach Mark Keenan, who won the 1994 Promotions Cup as Ireland captain.
articles.content:
IRELAND HAVE WON the FIBA European Championship for Small Countries, after a 97-66 victory over Malta.
